{"title":"3T brings carbon frame production home to Italy, complete with custom filament winding & Founder’s Edition","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/16/3t-brings-carbon-frame-production-home-to-italy-complete-with-custom-filament-winding/","date":1623858374000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Back in 2019,<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/11/21/factory-tour-inside-3t-cycling-how-torno-carbon-cranks-are-handmade-in-italy-more/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> we visited 3T to get a first hand look</a> at how their Torno carbon cranks were being produced. While the emphasis was on the crankset construction, 3T hinted that Italian-made frames would be a possibility some time in the near future. The pandemic may have slowed things down a bit, but 3T has just officially announced their move into Italian-made framesets, and they’ll be offering a Founders Edition to celebrate.</p><h2>Dry Fiber with Resin Injection</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x726/rscb18/ng:webp/ngcb18\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production carbon fibers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-200x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-800x1200.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-80x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-768x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-1024x1536.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-696x1044.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-1068x1602.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-280x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x726/rscb18/ng:webp/ngcb18\" ezoid=\"0.266718535053019\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-200x300.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-800x1200.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-80x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-768x1152.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-1024x1536.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-696x1044.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-1068x1602.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104736/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-1-280x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb18 280w\"></a></p><p>Just how do you go about making your own carbon frames in house? For 3T, it was a step by step learning process which started with the Torno crankset. To keep things simple, the Torno started with more standard carbon fiber sheets, but with so called ‘dry fiber’. That means that unlike preimpregnated carbon fiber, the resin hasn’t been added yet. 3T claims that this allows for the creation of more complex shapes, while also opening up more types of carbon fiber to be used.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production layup\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104859/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-19-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production in mold\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-h