2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104755/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-5-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Another big advantage is that dry fiber frames can be placed directly into hot molds without the resin starting to immediately cure. This saves time and energy from constantly warming and cooling each mold before use. Then, once the frame is inside the mold, the resin is injected and cured, which with the right technique, results in a better surface finish without the need for huge amounts of hand finishing.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production with filament winding\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-I