ouse-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104828/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-13-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a>Additionally, the dry fiber has advantages that 3T was planning to utilize when they made the move to frame production. Deciding that filament winding was the way to go to create carbon layups without limitations for fiber angles, they have gone to great lengths to develop their own custom filament winding machines.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production in mold\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-ho