loads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104800/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-7-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>By using dry fiber, 3T says that they have access to “every grade and type of carbon fiber” as a dry fiber yarn. That gives them more options when it comes to the exact type of carbon fiber used in the frame production, and helps them configure their ideal layup and ride qualities.</p><p>3T points out that the filament winders shown above are prototypes – they’re not showing the final versions. For obvious reasons.</p><h2>First Frames</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production complete bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104849/3t-in-house-carbon-manufacturing-made-in-Italy-frames-17-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>In 2019 (right around the time of Cory’s visit), they started the development of their first&nbsp; carbon frame – the Racemax Italia. They figured that if they could create a lighter frame than their current top of the line option with the same stiffness and strength, they could do just about anything. Now, that dream has become reality.</p><h2>Founder’s Edition</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2.jpg\" alt=\"3T Italian frameset production founder's edition\" width=\"1200\" height=\"672\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-297x166.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-800x448.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-120x67.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-768x430.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-696x390.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-1068x598.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-750x420.jpg 750w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-297x166.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-800x448.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-120x67.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-768x430.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-696x390.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-1068x598.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16104911/Founders-Edition-1600x896-2-750x420.jpg 750w\"></a></p><p>To celebrate the occasion, 3T is offering the first 100 Italian-made frames as a special Founder’s Edition. Well, the first 99 frames – frame #001 is going into their museum.</p><p>These very special bikes will be sold as a frameset with fork, seatpost, and some special Founder’s Edition touches:</p><ul><li>Engraved metal limited edition plaque with frame number</li><li>Custom see-through paint options</li><li>2 finish options under the see-through paint (standard or industrial carbon finish, see below)</li><li>Customer’s name under the clearcoat</li><li>1X+2X frame or dedicated 1X frame (perfectly smooth seattube without any inserts for an FD mount)</li></ul><p>3T promises more details and photos at a later date, but they point out that bikes will be delivered in order, so the earlier you get your order in, the sooner you’ll get the bike. The Founders Edition can be ordered from 3T’s top Experience Centers and from 3T directly for USD $5,999 (+tax) / EUR 5,999 (incl. tax) / GBP 5,499 (incl. tax). The link below has a contact form for 3T for more details, with production slated from now through October.</p><p><a href=\"https://blog.3t.bike/2021/06/17365/frame-building-is-coming-home/?_ke=eyJrbF9jb21wYW55X2lkIjogIlRKMmFWWiIsICJrbF9lbWFpbCI6ICJ6YWNoQGJpa2VydW1vci5jb20ifQ%3D%3D\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>3t.bike</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"767794b5a9ea8830da7c4f4d62aecfdc17f5052dd455dda2e37ee688800eaf21","category":"Cycling"}